  "script": "A team just built the tallest sandcastle in history, and it stands taller than a three-story building. It took a crew weeks, thousands of tons of sand, and a small army of sculptors packing and carving layer after layer. Sand is deceptively hard to build tall with; too dry and it crumbles, too wet and it slumps, so they mixed it to the exact right dampness and compacted every layer like concrete. The finished tower had spiral ramps, tiny windows, and detailed turrets all the way up. One good rainstorm could erase the whole thing. So how tall can a pile of sand actually go?",
